    "day_number": 1,
    "title": "To Be (am / is / are)",
    "explanation": "The verb 'to be' is one of the most important verbs in English. It has three forms in the present: am, is, and are.\n\nUse 'am' with I.\nUse 'is' with he, she, it, and singular nouns.\nUse 'are' with you, we, they, and plural nouns.\n\nTo make a negative sentence, add 'not' after the verb: am not, is not (isn't), are not (aren't).\n\nTo make a question, put the verb before the subject: Am I...? Is he...? Are you...?",
    "examples": [
      {
        "sentence": "I am a student.",
        "note": "I + am"
      },
      {
        "sentence": "She is from Tashkent.",
        "note": "She + is"
      },
      {
        "sentence": "They are my friends.",
        "note": "They + are"
      },
      {
        "sentence": "He is not happy today.",
        "note": "negative: is not = isn't"
      },
      {
        "sentence": "Are you ready?",
        "note": "question: Are + you"
      }
    ],
